O:9:"MagpieRSS":18:{s:6:"parser";i:0;s:12:"current_item";a:0:{}s:5:"items";a:15:{i:0;a:8:{s:5:"title";s:54:"USGS Nevada Water Science Center Welcomes New Director";s:8:"category";s:92:"PRNR2016_02_22 water CenterDirector DavidBerger 
CarsonCity NevadaWaterScienceCeneter Nevada";s:4:"link";s:57:"http://www.usgs.gov/newsroom/article.asp?ID=4459&from=rss";s:6:"georss";a:2:{s:14:"featuretypetag";s:5:"state";s:11:"featurename";s:2:"NV";}s:11:"description";s:3220:"
						
						
					
						
						<!--summarystart-->
						<strong>Summary:</strong> 





David Berger is the new Director of the USGS Nevada Water Science Center, headquartered in Carson City.



CARSON CITY, Nev. &mdash; David Berger begins work today as Director of the U.S. Geological Survey's Nevada Water Science Center, headquartered in Carson City.
						<hr size="1">
						<!--summaryend-->
		<p><strong>Contact Information:</strong></p>
		<p>
		
					<a href="mailto:rmcclymont@usgs.gov">Ryan &nbsp;McClymont</a>
			  			
			
			( Phone: 503-251-3237
		); 
		
		
</p>
<br>
