satellite FogBelt coast";s:4:"link";s:57:"http://www.usgs.gov/newsroom/article.asp?ID=4454&from=rss";s:6:"georss";a:2:{s:14:"featuretypetag";s:5:"state";s:11:"featurename";s:2:"CA";}s:11:"description";s:4264:"
						
						
					
						
						<!--summarystart-->
						<strong>Summary:</strong> A new series of maps of fog and low clouds covering the northern and central California coasts reveals daytime and nighttime patterns with a level of detail never previously mapped. U.S. Geological Survey scientists used new analyses of satellite images to understand the dynamics of fog.&nbsp;
						<hr size="1">
						<!--summaryend-->
		<p><strong>Contact Information:</strong></p>
		<p>
		
					<a href="mailto:lgordon@usgs.gov">Leslie &nbsp;Gordon</a>
			  			
			
