						<strong>Summary:</strong> TACOMA, Wash. &mdash; The Sumas River, in northwest Washington, contains sediment that carries naturally occurring asbestos. This week, scientists at the U.S. Geological Survey, in cooperation with the U.S. Environmental Protection Agency, released a report detailing new and publicly available information about the asbestos in the water and sediment.&nbsp;
