						<strong>Summary:</strong> Globally there were 14,588 earthquakes of magnitude 4.0 or greater in 2015. &nbsp;This worldwide number is on par with prior year averages of about 40 earthquakes per day of magnitude 4.0, or about 14,500 annually. &nbsp;The 2015 number may change slightly as the final results are completed by seismic analysts at the USGS National Earthquake Information Center in Golden, Colorado.
						<hr size="1">
						<!--summaryend-->
		<p><strong>Contact Information:</strong></p>
		<p>
		
					<a href="mailto:hkoontz@usgs.gov">Heidi &nbsp;Koontz </a>
			  			
			
			( Phone: 303-202-4763
		); 
		
		
